g.text: - Changed RegOutpADCD1ECR,RegInpADCD1PER, RegOutpADCD0ECR,RegOutpADCD1ECR datatype to U08
- Change ADC parity function to run periodically.
- Pass 0 to Parameter Byte output in state based handling for states 1,3,5,7.
- Change the pass and fail steps for NTCs 0x032 & 0x033 to calibrations instead of config params
- Change sequence of state handling in AdcDiagcPer1. State update should happen last.
- Replaced stateflow with equivalent simulink blocks
- Requirements linkage added on new blocks
- Per1 Adc Diagc Pointer block executes state 6 handling for all cases where Adc Diag State != 0, 2 or 4. Added
elseif condition for handling of state 6.
- Same block needs to send StrtPtr and EndPtr to PIM to hold values between states 0,2,4,6
- The StrPtr and EndPtr PIMs should be read to update the outputs from the Adc Daigc Pointer block in Per1.
- Remove 'MotCtrl' prefix from I/O not connected to motor control ISR
- Change diagnostic parameters on AdcFltCntSt datastores for MIL testing
- Change register utilized for parity error check from APDPERRST to ADCDnPER
- Change register utilized for parity error clear from APDPERRSTC to ADCDnECR
- Add 4 outputs for ADCn start and end pointers (2 per ADC unit). This change also
server functions utilized in CM300A and CM320A
- Add diagnostics for ADC reference read at the beginning and end of scan groups 2 & 3. Utilize NTC
- As per Anomaly CR EA4#3686, the Input Voltage ~= 0 condtion has been changed with
Input Voltage greater than ARCHGLBPRM_FLOATZEROTHD_ULS_F32 in the CM340A_AdcDiagc_Library's
zero check subsystem. ARCHGLBPRM_FLOATZEROTHD_ULS_F32 variable is defined in the .m file.
-As per Anomaly CR EA4#3836, SetAdc0ParFlt,SetAdc1ParFlt server runnables have been merged to "SetAdcParFlt".
and logic related to these has been added
- As per Anomaly CR EA4#4188, fault determination logic has been updated.
8-new PIMs have been created to store fault accumulation avalue in each state for ADC0 and ADC1
All changes are highlighted in the red color.
